training_organizations.name: Kentucky Cabinet for Health & Family Services Training Consortium
training_organizations.description: Kentucky’s CHFS partners with universities (like University of Kentucky and others) in a training consortium to educate child welfare staff. This consortium develops and delivers curriculum for new Social Service Workers and ongoing training for experienced staff, aiming for a consistent, professional approach across the state.

training_organizations.name: Sunrise Children’s Services
training_organizations.description: A faith-based nonprofit organization in Kentucky that contracts with CHFS to provide foster care and residential treatment services. Sunrise operates therapeutic foster homes and several residential facilities, caring for children with behavioral or emotional needs. It recruits foster families (often through churches) and works with the state to place children who need specialized care.

training_organizations.name: Necco
training_organizations.description: A private foster care and counseling agency active in Kentucky (and neighboring states). Necco contracts with Kentucky to recruit and train foster parents and to supervise foster placements, particularly for youth requiring therapeutic foster care. Necco also offers behavioral health services to support children in foster care and their caregivers.
